        <body>
      
		<pb n="1"/>
			<p rend="align(right)"><placeName>St Thomas</placeName> <date>6 Sep 1852</date></p>
			<p><addressee>Revd. I Leeser</addressee></p>
          <p rend="indent(2)">My Dr Sir</p>
          <p rend="indent(4)">I am in receipt of your various<lb/> letters with the missing Occidents &#38; those up to <date>August</date>.<lb/> I found them very interesting&#8212;I delivered your letter to <persName>Mr<lb/> Simmonds</persName> who is as you will perceive alive. I spoke to one of<lb/> his subscribers as to the payments&#44; he only owes for the present<lb/> year.</p>
          <p rend="indent(1)">The Government have extended to these <placeName>Islands</placeName> a<lb/> representative assembly to be held yearly at <placeName>St Croix</placeName>&#44; the vote for<lb/> Representation of the three <placeName>Islands</placeName> to be held in at each<lb/> <placeName>Island</placeName> on the same day. The Governor who <add>&#63;</add> the day<lb/> of election resides at <placeName>St Croix</placeName> which <del>he</del> is head Quarters&#44;<lb/> the day of the first election was <add>&#63;</add> by him for <date>Saturday<lb/> the 28</date> &#38; it was announced in our news paper on the <date>22<hi rend="sup">d</hi></date>. I<lb/> immediately wrote a Christian friend at <placeName>St Croix</placeName> to call<lb/> on His <add>&#63;</add> for me &#38; state that I was persuaded he<lb/> did not recollect that <date>Saturday</date> was the Jewish<lb/> <date>Sabbath</date> &#38; that would preclude many Israelites <del>from</del><lb/> voting&#44; that I was appointed one of the Judges <del>of</del> at the<lb/> Poll which I would have to decline. His Excellency<lb/> replied to my friend that he saw the propriety of<lb/> altering the day &#38; <add>&#63;</add> it for <date>Monday the 30 August</date><lb/> will you insert this in the Chronicle in good stile. I<lb/> think it should commence with &#8220;Justice &#38; liberality.&#8221; I see<lb/> <add>&#63;</add> by experience&#44; that if we respect ourselves we will<lb/> be respected for your information I had 32 votes &#38; would<lb/> have been one of the Representatives had not the Directors of<lb/> the Bank used their influence with the voters&#44; to prevent my</p>
		<pb n="2"/>
			<p><sic>my</sic> return&#44; stating as the reason that my services were<lb/> <sic>indispensible</sic> to the Bank. Many happy holy days&#8212;</p>
          <p rend="indent(1)">Yours truly</p>
          <p rend="indent(2)"><persName role="author">A Wolff</persName></p>
			<p>I am happy to find you have<lb/> progressed so well with the Bible&#44; the type appears<lb/> to be very good &#38; the printing distinct</p>
		<pb n="3"/>
			<p><addressee>Revd Mr I Leeser</addressee></p>
          <p rend="indent(2)"><placeName>Philada</placeName></p>
          
        </body>
